I will never shop here again. I had the unfortunate experience of having my card not work at the register. The cashier rudely demanded I pay another way. I explained I couldn’t, I showed her my ample balance online and explained that I didn’t know why the card wouldn’t work, but I couldn’t pay another way. I only brought that one card. She gave me a horrible look of disgust and then looked away and laughed to herself. I apologized, excused myself and left.  I was a block away only to have a stock boy chase me down the street SCREAMING as though I had stolen something. I turned and he demanded, “You have to come back” in front of a small crowd of people. I said simply, “Why?”. I wasn’t carrying any bags. I hadn’t taken anything. They just chose to treat me like a thief to humiliate me I guess?! The man didn’t acknowledge my question at all. He just turned and left because he clearly had ZERO reason to demand my presence in their store. He also didn’t apologize for the clearly needless harassment.  I will never ever step foot inside again.  Fortunately, I have means, and I didn’t go hungry that night- I just shopped somewhere else. But I can’t imagine how much more awful that experience would have been if I truly had nothing, and had just found that out at the register only to be treated like a criminal for simply leaving. Being poor isn’t a crime. If someone leaves your store because they can’t afford something, that doesn’t give you the right to treat them like a thief.  I’m a privileged person, but accusing a man of theft in a grocery store just got a Black man MURDERED by the police.  STOP CRIMINALIZING POVERTY WESTSIDE MARKET!!!
